nati]]''\n| {{Nom}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/siima-awards-2019-heres-a-complete-list-of-nominees/articleshow/70287216.cms|title=SIIMA Awards 2019: Here's a complete list of nominees - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=18 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190801183932/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/siima-awards-2019-heres-a-complete-list-of-nominees/articleshow/70287216.cms|archive-date=1 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[66th Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Award South]]\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor \u2013 Telugu|Best Actor \u2013 Telugu]]\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/features/nominations-for-the-66th-filmfare-awards-south-2019_-37931.html|title=Nominations for the 66th Filmfare Awards (South) 2019|website=[[Filmfare]]|accessdate=23 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212141500/https://www.filmfare.com/features/nominations-for-the-66th-filmfare-awards-south-2019_-37931.html|archive-date=12 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor \u2013 South | Best Actor (Critics) \u2013 Telugu]]\n| {{won}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/66th-yamaha-fascino-filmfare-awards-south-full-list-of-winners-in-telugu-cinema/articleshow/72920660.cms|title=66th Yamaha Fascino Filmfare Awards South: Full List of Winners in Telugu Cinema - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=22 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222053917/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/66th-yamaha-fascino-filmfare-awards-south-full-list-of-winners-in-telugu-cinema/articleshow/72920660.cms|archive-date=22 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name|4921260}}\n\n{{FilmfareSouthCriticsBestActor}}\n{{Kerala State Film Award for Best Actor}}\n{{SIIMA Award for Best Male D\u00e9butante}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Salmaan, Dulquer}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Telugu cinema]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Kochi]]\n[[Category:Indian Muslims]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards South winners]]\n[[Category:Purdue University alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:SIIMA Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Kerala State Film Award winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian actor}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Dulquer Salmaan\n| image              = Dulquer Salmaan at Karwaan promotions (cropped).jpg\n| caption            = Dulquer Salmaan promoting ''[[Karwaan]]'' in 2018\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1986|07|28}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmfare.com/features/happy-birthday-dq-14782.html|title=Happy Birthday DQ!|work=[[Filmfare]]|date=28 July 2016|author=Devesh Sharma|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160730044023/http://www.filmfare.com/features/happy-birthday-dq-14782.html|archivedate=30 July 2016}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n| nationality        = Indian\n| alma_mater         = [[Purdue University]]\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|playback singer|businessman|film producer}}\n| years_active       = 2012\u2013present\n| height             = \n| spouse             = {{marriage|Amal Sufiya|2011}}\n| children           = 1\n| parents            = [[Mammootty]] (father)\n| relatives          = [[Maqbool Salmaan]] (cousin)\n| website            = {{url|http://www.dulquer.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Dulquer Salmaan''' (born 28 July 1986), is an Indian film actor, playback singer and film producer who predominantly works in [[Malayalam]] language films. He has also worked in [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]] and [[Hindi]] language films. The son of actor [[Mammootty]], Dulquer graduated with a bachelor's degree in Business Management from [[Purdue University]], and worked as a business manager before pursuing a career in acting. He is the winner of four [[Filmfare Awards South]] and one [[Kerala State Film Awards]].\n\nAfter a three-month acting course at the [[Barry John]] Acting Studio, he made his debut in the 2012 action drama ''[[Second Show]]'', for which he received the [[Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut \u2013 South|Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut]]. He received his first [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor \u2013 Malayalam|Filmfare Award for Best Actor]] nomination for his performance in ''[[Ustad Hotel]]'' (2012).\n\nAfter the commercial success of the comedy ''[[ABCD: American-Born Confused Desi]]'' (2013) and the road thriller ''[[Neelakasham Pachakadal Chuvanna Bhoomi]]'' (2013), Salmaan appeared in the [[Tamil language|Tamil]] romantic comedy ''[[Vaayai Moodi Pesavum]]'' (2014). He then starred in the ensemble romantic drama ''[[Bangalore Days]]'' (2014), which ranks among the [[List of highest-grossing Malayalam films|highest-grossing Malayalam films]]. He achieved further success in Tamil cinema with [[Mani Ratnam]]'s critically and commercially successful romance ''[[O Kadhal Kanmani]]'' (2015). Subsequently, Salmaan garnered acclaim for portraying the title role in the 2015 romantic drama ''[[Charlie (2015 Malayalam film)|Charlie]]'', winning him the [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actor]]. He appeared in the Telugu biopic ''[[Mahanati]]'' (2018) and in the Hindi films ''[[Karwaan]]'' (2018) and ''[[The Zoya Factor (film)|The Zoya Factor]]'' (2019).\n\nSalmaan has been recognised in the media as a fashion icon.<ref name=\"Manorama Online\">{{cite web|url=http://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/how-dulquer-salmaan-is-emerging-as-an-undisputed-youth-icon.html|title=10 reasons why Dulquer Salmaan is emerging as an undisputed youth icon|work=[[Malayala Manorama]]|date=23 April 2016|author=Padmakumar K|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630051538/http://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/how-dulquer-salmaan-is-emerging-as-an-undisputed-youth-icon.html|archivedate=30 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Times-50-Most-Desirable-Men-2014/articleshow/47071834.cms |title=Times 50 Most Desirable Men 2014 |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=28 April 2015 |author=Priya Gupta |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150711070657/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Times-50-Most-Desirable-Men-2014/articleshow/47071834.cms |archivedate=11 July 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}<br>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-dulquer-samantha-are-style-icons-imagegallery-kollywood-pcckpGdbcjhij.html |title=Vikram, Dulquer, Samantha are style icons! |publisher=[[Sify]] |date=28 April 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150513004904/http://www.sify.com/movies/vikram-dulquer-samantha-are-style-icons-imagegallery-kollywood-pcckpGdbcjhij.html |archivedate=13 May 2015 }}<br>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/Dulquer-to-Prithviraj-Five-young-Mollywood-actors-to-watch-out-for/Dulquer-to-Prithviraj-Five-young-Mollywood-actors-to-watch-out-for/photostory/49148114.cms |title=Dulquer to Prithviraj: Five young Mollywood actors to watch out for |work=The Times of India |date=29 September 2015 |author=Jessy John |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924164140/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/Dulquer-to-Prithviraj-Five-young-Mollywood-actors-to-watch-out-for/photostory/49148123.cms |archivedate=24 September 2016 }}<br>{{cite web|url=http://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/dulquer-salmaan-among-the-50-most-influential-young-indians.html |title=Proud moment: Dulquer Salmaan among the 50 most influential young Indians |work=Malayala Manorama |date=3 July 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160704125652/http://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/dulquer-salmaan-among-the-50-most-influential-young-indians.html |archivedate=4 July 2016 }}<br>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/5-Looks-of-Dulquer-Salmaan-which-proves-he-is-a-fashion-icon/5-Looks-of-Dulquer-Salmaan-which-proves-he-is-a-fashion-icon/photostory/52556315.cms |title=5 Looks of Dulquer Salmaan which proves he is a fashion icon |work=The Times of India |date=2 June 2016 |author=Benson Philip |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924164435/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/5-Looks-of-Dulquer-Salmaan-which-proves-he-is-a-fashion-icon/photostory/52556336.cms |archivedate=24 September 2016 }}</ref> He owns several [[entrepreneurship]] ventures and promotes various social causes.\n\n==Early life==\nDulquer Salmaan was born on 28 July 1986 in India.<ref name=\"DoB\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/happy-birthday-dulquer-salmaan-rare-pictures-ok-kanmani-actor-640745|title=Happy Birthday Dulquer Salmaan: 'OK Kanmani' Actor Thanks Fans For Wishes|publisher=[[International Business Times]]|date=28 July 2015|author=Sushmita Sen|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305082156/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/happy-birthday-dulquer-salmaan-rare-pictures-ok-kanmani-actor-640745| archivedate=5 March 2016}}</ref> Salmaan is the second child of actor [[Mammootty]] and his wife Sulfath. He has an elder sister, Surumi. He completed his [[Primary education|primary level education]] at [[Toc-H Public School]], [[Vyttila]], Kochi and his [[Secondary education|secondary level education]] at [[Sishya School]] in [[Chennai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indulge.newindianexpress.com/a-brand-new-salmaan/chennai/7236|title=A brand new Salmaan|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=28 February 2014|author=Surya Praphulla Kumar|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160623193542/http://indulge.newindianexpress.com/a-brand-new-salmaan/chennai/7236 | archivedate=23 June 2016}}</ref> He then moved to the United States and earned a bachelor's degree in [[Bachelor of Business Management|Business Management]] from [[Purdue University]]. After graduation, he worked in the U.S. and later did an [[Information Technology|I.T.]]-related business in Dubai. He decided later to pursue a career in acting and attended a three-month course at the [[Barry John (theatre director)|Barry John]] Acting Studio in [[Mumbai]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/article337960.ece|title=Living under a cinematic giant| work=The New Indian Express|date=29 January 2012|author=Shevlin Sebastian|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160623202031/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/article337960.ece|archivedate=23 June 2016}}</ref> He stated in a 2012 interview that he chose acting because \" ... somewhere down the lane, my life became monotonous and routine\".<ref name=\"DQbefSS\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/i-want-to-go-step-by-step-dulquer-salmaan-news-malayalam-mcblBBhhdiasi.html|title=I want to go step by step: Dulquer Salmaan|publisher=Sify|date=3 February 2012|author=Sridevi Sreedhar|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701125513/http://www.sify.com/movies/i-want-to-go-step-by-step-dulquer-salmaan-news-malayalam-mcblBBhhdiasi.html|archivedate=1 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Film career==\n===Debut, breakthrough and stardom (2012\u201313)===\nIn 2011, Salmaan signed on for debutante Srinath Rajendran's ''[[Second Show]]'' (2012) in which he played the role of Harilal, a gangster. When asked in an interview about his \"unconventional entry with a bunch of newcomers\", Salmaan stated that it was his conscious decision as he felt that \" ... when an actor debuts, he has to earn the right to be a hero and not get it through a shortcut route.\"<ref name=\"DQbefSS\" /> The film received mixed reviews.<ref name=\"Retrosp\">{{cite web|title=From 'Second Show' to 'Charlie': A look into Dulquer Salmaan's acting career of 4 years|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/second-show-charlie-look-into-dulquer-salmaans-acting-career-4-years-665575|publisher=International Business Times|date=3 February 2016|author=Anu James|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160214161032/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/second-show-charlie-look-into-dulquer-salmaans-acting-career-4-years-665575|archivedate=14 February 2016}}</ref> A critic for [[Sify]] stated, \" ... it is Salmaan's amazing screen presence and a matured acting style that makes the movie an engaging watch\",<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Second Show|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/second-show-review-malayalam-pcmaoFgdgefic.html|publisher=Sify|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701131019/http://www.sify.com/movies/second-show-review-malayalam-pcmaoFgdgefic.html|archivedate=1 July 2016}}</ref> while Paresh C Palicha of [[Rediff]] criticised his performance. \"There is no denying that he looks dapper and has an attractive baritone (a gift of his gene pool). But that does not translate into good performance or acting.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Second Show is disappointing |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/south-review-second-show-is-disappointing/20120206.htm |publisher=Rediff |date=6 February 2012|author=Paresh C. Palicha|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150720031202/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/south-review-second-show-is-disappointing/20120206.htm|archivedate=20 July 2015}}</ref> The film was commercially successful and won him the [[Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut \u2013 South|Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/second-show-celebrates-100-days-news-malayalam-mgtiFncdaei.html|title=Second Show celebrates 100 days|publisher=Sify|date=19 June 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022024154/http://www.sify.com/movies/second-show-celebrates-100-days-news-malayalam-mgtiFncdaei.html|archivedate=22 October 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"r1ff\" />\n\nSalmaan next starred in [[Anwar Rasheed]]'s ''[[Ustad Hotel]]'' (2012). The film, which received the [[National Film Award for Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment]], was also a major success at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-malayalam-films-strike-gold-at-the-national-awards/20130320.htm|title=Malayalam films strike gold at the National Awards|publisher=Rediff|date=20 March 2013|author=Shobha Warrier|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229235937/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-south-malayalam-films-strike-gold-at-the-national-awards/20130320.htm|archivedate=29 February 2016}}</ref> He also won praise for his portrayal of Faizy.<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Ustad Hotel offers a delicious meal |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-ustad-hotel-offers-a-delicious-meal/20120702.htm |author=Paresh C. Palicha |publisher=Rediff |date=2 July 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304041318/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-ustad-hotel-offers-a-delicious-meal/20120702.htm |archivedate=4 March 2016}}<br>{{cite web|title=Movie Review: Ustad Hotel |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/ustad-hotel-review-malayalam-15001974.html |publisher=Sify |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140327001030/http://www.sify.com/movies/ustad-hotel-review-malayalam-15001974.html |archivedate=27 March 2014}}</ref> Anil R Nair, writing for ''[[The New Indian Express]]'', stated, \"The youthful and glamorous Dulquer has come out of his father\u2019s shadow in the role of Faisi.\"<ref>{{cite web|title='Ustad Hotel' (Malayalam)|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/reviews/article555983.ece |work=The New Indian Express|date=3 July 2012|author=Anil R Nair|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160324221043/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/reviews/article555983.ece|archivedate=24 March 2016}}</ref> For his performance, Salmaan received his first nomination for the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor \u2013 Malayalam|Filmfare Award for Best Actor]].<ref name=\"UHNom\" /> His third film was ''[[Theevram]]'', a crime thriller directed by [[Roopesh Peethambaran]]. The film, which released on November 2012, received mixed reviews and was a box office failure.<ref>{{cite web|title=Malayalam movie 'Theevram' to have its sequel|url=http://www.news18.com/news/india/malayalam-movie-theevram-to-have-its-sequel-525961.html|work=[[CNN-News18]] |date=10 December 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160624113356/http://www.news18.com/news/india/malayalam-movie-theevram-to-have-its-sequel-525961.html|archivedate=24 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Dulquar.jpg|thumb|upright|Salmaan at the 2013 [[Filmfare Awards South]]]]\n\nIn 2013, he signed on to appear in [[Martin Prakkat]]'s comedy drama ''[[ABCD: American-Born Confused Desi]]'' in which he made his singing debut with \"Johnny Mone Johnny\". Both the song and the film became popular.<ref name=\"Retrosp\" /><ref name=\"Patt\">{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/racing-ahead/article5221122.ece|title=Racing ahead|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=10 October 2013|author=Saraswathy Nagarajan|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131013045930/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/racing-ahead/article5221122.ece|archivedate=13 October 2013}}</ref> Though the film received mixed reviews, his performance was well received by critics. Sify stated: \"it is Dulquer Salmaan's show all the way and in all fairness the young actor has given his heart and soul into his character.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Review : ABCD|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/abcd-review-malayalam-pcmaRMdbbabbi.html|publisher=Sify|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701132524/http://www.sify.com/movies/abcd-review-malayalam-pcmaRMdbbabbi.html|archivedate=1 July 2016}}</ref> He was also part of [[Amal Neerad]]'s segment ''Kullante Bharya'' in the anthology film ''[[5 Sundarikal]]'' (2013).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/malayalam/news-and-interviews/Dulquer-Reenu-in-Amal-Neerads-Anju-Sundarikal/articleshow/18399738.cms|title=Dulquer, Reenu in Amal Neerad's 'Anju Sundarikal' \u2013 Times Of India|author=Ammu Zachariah|date=9 February 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022064857/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/malayalam/news-and-interviews/Dulquer-Reenu-in-Amal-Neerads-Anju-Sundarikal/articleshow/18399738.cms\n|archivedate=22 October 2014|work=[[The Times of India]]}}</ref> The film was critically acclaimed, with praise specially directed towards ''Kullante Bharya''. Aswin J. Kumar of ''[[The Times of India]]'' wrote, \" ... it's the tale of the nameless woman, 'Kullante Bharya' that stays with the viewer.\" He also praised Salmaan's performance as a photographer who was bound to his wheelchair.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movie-reviews/Anchu-Sundarikal/movie-review/20723763.cms |title=Anchu Sundarikal Movie Review |work=The Times of India |author=Aswin J. Kumar |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20160730054511/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movie-reviews/Anchu-Sundarikal/movie-review/20723763.cms |archivedate=30 July 2016}}</ref> Salmaan then collaborated with [[Sameer Thahir]] in ''[[Neelakasham Pachakadal Chuvanna Bhoomi]]'' (2013), a road movie.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/dulquer-sunny-wayne-starts-another-journey-together-news-malayalam-nb4pFrfjcgb.html|title=Dulquer, Sunny Wayne starts another journey together|publisher=Sify|date=30 January 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303073238/http://www.sify.com/movies/dulquer-sunny-wayne-starts-another-journey-together-news-malayalam-nb4pFrfjcgb.html|archivedate=3 March 2016}}</ref> The film and his performance was appreciated.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=pl4rahbchbabe|title=Kerala Box-Office \u2013 Eid Weekend \u2013 August 9 to 11|publisher=Sify|date=13 August 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701132526/http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=pl4rahbchbabe|archivedate=1 July 2016}}</ref> Salmaan starred in his \"first love story\", cinematographer [[Alagappan N|Alagappan]]'s romantic drama ''[[Pattam Pole]]'' (2013), co-starring debutante [[Malavika Mohanan]]. The film was a commercial failure.<ref name=\"Patt\" /><ref name=\"DQBM\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Nivin-Dulquer-Prithvi-and-Fahadh-the-new-stars-of-Malayalam-cinema/articleshow/47577494.cms|title=Nivin, Dulquer, Prithvi and Fahadh, the new stars of Malayalam cinema|work=[[Bangalore Mirror]]|date=7 June 2015|author=Sethumadhavan N |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150912141626/http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Nivin-Dulquer-Prithvi-and-Fahadh-the-new-stars-of-Malayalam-cinema/articleshow/47577494.cms|archivedate=12 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n===2014\u2013present===\nIn 2014, Salmaan took on another romantic role in ''[[Salalah Mobiles]]'', with [[Nazriya Nazim]] opposite him; like ''Pattam Pole'', ''Salalah Mobiles'' could not garner much success for the actor.<ref name=\"DQBM\"/> Salmaan's next appearance was in the Tamil-Malayalam bilingual ''[[Vaayai Moodi Pesavum]]'' (2014). While the Malayalam version ''[[Samsaaram Aarogyathinu Haanikaram]]'' was received poorly, the Tamil version received positive reviews and became a [[sleeper hit]].<ref name=\"2014Ret\">{{cite news|title=Tinsel town: The year of the underdogs|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/tinsel-town-the-year-of-the-underdogs/article6730338.ece|newspaper=The Hindu|date=27 December 2014|author=M. P. Praveen|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160730055204/http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/tinsel-town-the-year-of-the-underdogs/article6730338.ece|archivedate=30 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vaayai-moodi-pesavum-the-surprise-sleeper-hit-news-tamil-ofqo04ggiddsi.html|title='Vaayai Moodi Pesavum', the surprise sleeper hit|publisher=Sify|date=16 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701135609/http://www.sify.com/movies/vaayai-moodi-pesavum-the-surprise-sleeper-hit-news-tamil-ofqo04ggiddsi.html|archivedate=1 July 2016}}</ref> [[Indo-Asian News Service|IANS]] said Salmaan is \"a treat to watch\" and added, \"he earns extra brownie points for dubbing in his own voice and speaking flawless Tamil.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/vaayai-moodi-pesavum-sometimes-brilliant-sometimes-contradictory-ians-tamil-movie-review-114042600377_1.html|title='Vaayai Moodi Pesavum' - sometimes brilliant, sometimes contradictory|agency=[[Indo-Asian News Service|IANS]]|work=[[Business Standard]]|date=27 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701185749/http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/vaayai-moodi-pesavum-sometimes-brilliant-sometimes-contradictory-ians-tamil-movie-review-114042600377_1.html|archivedate=1 July 2016}}</ref> He received his second Filmfare Award for Best Male Debut for the film.<ref name=\"Filmfare\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/winners-of-62nd-britannia-filmfare-awards-south-9643.html|title=Winners of 62nd Britannia Filmfare Awards South|work=Filmfare|date=27 June 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129092825/http://www.filmfare.com/news/winners-of-62nd-britannia-filmfare-awards-south-9643.html|archivedate=29 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Anjali Menon]]'s ensemble romantic comedy drama ''[[Bangalore Days]]'' (2014), Salmaan played Arjun with [[Nivin Pauly]] and [[Nazriya Nazim]] as his cousins. The film received positive reviews and emerged as [[List of highest-grossing Malayalam films|one of the highest-grossing Malayalam films of all time]], grossing around {{INRConvert|500|m}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/No-Hyderabad-days-yet/articleshow/45781766.cms |title=No Hyderabad days yet |date=6 January 2015 |work=Bangalore Mirror |author=S. S. Kamal |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150806110455/http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/No-Hyderabad-days-yet/articleshow/45781766.cms |archivedate= 6 August 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Later that year, he co-starred with [[Unni Mukundan]] in [[Lal Jose]]'s ''[[Vikramadithyan]]''. It was a commercial success.<ref name=\"2014Ret\" /> He then performed in what he called his \"most challenging film yet\" in [[Renjith]]'s ''[[Njaan]]'' (2014).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Njaan-is-the-most-challenging-film-yet-Dulquer/articleshow/36768883.cms|title=Njaan is the most challenging film yet: Dulquer|date=18 June 2015|work=The Times of India|author=Shiba Kurian|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140926045452/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Njaan-is-the-most-challenging-film-yet-Dulquer/articleshow/36768883.cms|archivedate=26 September 2014}}</ref> His performance received favourable reviews and earned him several accolades, including a second Best Actor nomination at Filmfare.<ref name=\"Retrosp\" /><ref name=\"FFNjaan\" />\n\nIn 2015, he acted opposite Nithya Menen in two films\u2014Jenuse Mohamed's romantic comedy ''[[100 Days of Love]]'', and [[Mani Ratnam]]'s Tamil romantic drama ''[[O Kadhal Kanmani]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title='Kanmani' of south India|url=http://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/interview/nithya-menen-kanmani-of-south-india.html|work=Malayala Manorama|date=2 June 2015|author=Juny Jacob|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160109151404/http://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/interview/nithya-menen-kanmani-of-south-india.html|archivedate=9 January 2016}}</ref> The latter opened to positive reviews and became successful at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/kanchana-2-and-ok-kanmani-are-super-hits-news-tamil-pevjEngjjhfde.html|title='Kanchana 2' and 'OK Kanmani' are super hits!|publisher=Sify|date=21 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151005050821/http://www.sify.com/movies/kanchana-2-and-ok-kanmani-are-super-hits-news-tamil-pevjEngjjhfde.html|archivedate=5 October 2015}}</ref> About Salmaan's performance, ''[[The Hindu]]'''s critic [[Baradwaj Rangan]] wrote: \"Dulquer Salmaan checks off all boxes in the Can You Be The Next [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]]? questionnaire\", though he believed the film belonged primarily to Menen.<ref>{{cite news|title=O Kadhal Kanmani: A lightweight but enjoyable romance|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/a-lightweight-but-enjoyable-romance/article7113868.ece|newspaper=The Hindu|date=17 April 2015|author=Baradwaj Rangan|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160730060035/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/a-lightweight-but-enjoyable-romance/article7113868.ece|archivedate=30 July 2016}}</ref> Salmaan next played the titular character in Martin Prakkat's ''[[Charlie (2015 Malayalam film)|Charlie]]'' (2015). The film generated a positive response from critics and received eight [[Kerala State Film Awards]], with Salmaan receiving his first Best Actor Award.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/kerala-state-film-awards/article8300123.ece|title='Charlie' sweeps Kerala State film awards; 'Ozhivudivasathe Kali' adjudged Best film|newspaper=The Hindu|date=1 March 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160730060245/http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/kerala-state-film-awards/article8300123.ece|archivedate=30 July 2016}}</ref> He also received a third Best Actor nomination at Filmfare.<ref name=\"Filmfare actor\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmfare.com/features/nominations-of-the-63rd-britannia-filmfare-awards-south-13750-3.html#descArticle|title=Nominations for the 63rd Britannia Filmfare Awards (South)|work=Filmfare|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160624143756/http://www.filmfare.com/features/nominations-of-the-63rd-britannia-filmfare-awards-south-13750-3.html|archivedate=24 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nSalmaan reunited with Sameer Thahir for his first release in 2016, ''[[Kali (2016 film)|Kali]]'' co-starring [[Sai Pallavi]]. When released, the film earned the highest opening day box office gross for a Malayalam film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/kerala-box-office-dulquer-salmaans-kali-becomes-top-malayalam-grosser-first-day-breaks-672501|title=Kerala box office: Dulquer Salmaan's 'Kali' becomes top Malayalam grosser on first day; breaks 'Charlie' records|publisher=International Business Times|date=29 March 2016|author=Anu James|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160413034255/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/kerala-box-office-dulquer-salmaans-kali-becomes-top-malayalam-grosser-first-day-breaks-672501|archivedate=13 April 2016}}</ref> He then starred in [[Rajeev Ravi]]'s crime drama ''[[Kammatipaadam]]'' (2016). The film garnered critical acclaim and became his third consecutive financial success in two years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/charlie-kali-kammatipaadam-dulquer-salmaan-gives-3-back-back-hits-kerala-box-office-681560#of2tCi1VvORlvwT0.97 |title='Charlie', 'Kali' and 'Kammatipaadam:' Dulquer Salmaan gives 3 back-to-back hits at Kerala box office |publisher=International Business Times |date=6 June 2016 |author=Anu James |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629153611/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/charlie-kali-kammatipaadam-dulquer-salmaan-gives-3-back-back-hits-kerala-box-office-681560 |archivedate=29 June 2016 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\nHe then appeared in [[Sathyan Anthikad]]'s family drama ''[[Jomonte Suvisheshangal]]'' (2017).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/jomonte-suviseshangal-review-fdfs-live-audience-response-ratings-dulquer-salmaan-sathyan-712805|title=Dulquer Salmaan's Jomonte Suvisheshangal review: Live audience updates|publisher=International Business Times|date=20 January 2017|author=Anu James|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122150455/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/jomonte-suviseshangal-review-fdfs-live-audience-response-ratings-dulquer-salmaan-sathyan-712805|archivedate=22 January 2017}}</ref> Despite comparisons with 2016 Malayalam drama ''[[Jacobinte Swargarajyam]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/jomonte-suvisheshangal-a-rip-off-of-jacobinte-swargarajyam-news-malayalam-rbyqK5hhehbge.html|title='Jomonte Suvisheshangal' a rip off of 'Jacobinte Swargarajyam'?|publisher=Sify|date=24 January 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170125134742/http://www.sify.com/movies/jomonte-suvisheshangal-a-rip-off-of-jacobinte-swargarajyam-news-malayalam-rbyqK5hhehbge.html|archivedate=25 January 2017}}</ref> the film did well commercially.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/kerala-box-office-munthirivallikal-thalirkkumbol-becomes-2nd-fastest-mohanlal-movie-cross-rs-20-714250|title=Kerala box office: Munthirivallikal Thalirkkumbol becomes 2nd fastest Mohanlal movie to cross Rs 20 crore mark|publisher=International Business Times|date=31 January 2017|author=Anu James|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170201080841/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/kerala-box-office-munthirivallikal-thalirkkumbol-becomes-2nd-fastest-mohanlal-movie-cross-rs-20-714250|archivedate=1 February 2017}}</ref> His next appearance was in [[Amal Neerad]]'s romantic action film ''[[Comrade In America]]'' (2017). ''The Hindu'' called it \"Dulquer's big hit of 2017\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Keeping up with Dulquer Salmaan|url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/keeping-up-with-dulquer-salmaan/article19736660.ece|newspaper=The Hindu|date=22 September 2017|author=Saraswathy Nagarajan|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923085902/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/keeping-up-with-dulquer-salmaan/article19736660.ece|archivedate=23 September 2017}}</ref> He then portrayed four roles in the bilingual anthology ''[[Solo (2017 film)|Solo]]'' (2017) directed by [[Bejoy Nambiar]]. The film was critically panned<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2017/oct/07/50-shades-of-dulquer-salmaan-i-enjoyed-playing-a-negative-character-in-solo-1667871.html|title=50 shades of Dulquer Salmaan: I enjoyed playing a negative character in 'Solo'|work=New Indian Express|date=8 October 2017|author=S Subhakeerthana|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171106132602/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2017/oct/07/50-shades-of-dulquer-salmaan-i-enjoyed-playing-a-negative-character-in-solo-1667871.html|archivedate=6 November 2017}}</ref> and \"faced immense backlash from the audience.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/regional/dulquer-salmaan-on-solo-climax-controversy-it-is-like-taking-away-creativity-from-an-artiste-4888959/|title=Dulquer Salmaan on Solo climax controversy: It is like taking away creativity from an artiste|work=Indian Express|date=16 October 2017|author=Ashameera Aiyappan|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171013190247/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/regional/dulquer-salmaan-on-solo-climax-controversy-it-is-like-taking-away-creativity-from-an-artiste-4888959/|archivedate=13 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe next featured in the bilingual ''[[Mahanati]]'', a biopic on actress [[Savitri (actress)|Savitri]]. His Telugu debut, the film opened to positive reviews from critics and enjoyed commercial success at the box office. Salmaan's portrayal of [[Gemini Ganeshan]] was also acclaimed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/keerthy-suresh-dulquer-salmaan-and-nag-ashwins-mahanati-rakes-in-staggering-trp/articleshow/65609367.cms|title=Keerthy Suresh, Dulquer Salmaan and Nag Ashwin's Mahanati rakes in staggering TRP|work=The Times of India|author=Neeshita Nyayapati|date=30 August 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180901152709/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/keerthy-suresh-dulquer-salmaan-and-nag-ashwins-mahanati-rakes-in-staggering-trp/articleshow/65609367.cms|archivedate=1 September 2018|access-date=1 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that year, Salmaan made his [[Hindi]] film debut with ''[[Karwaan]]''. Though the film received \"mixed response\", Salmaan's performance was appreciated.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-karwaan-actor-dulquer-salmaan-was-asked-if-he-would-do-a-biopic-on-his-father-mammootty-here-s-what-he-had-to-say-2646859|title='Karwaan' actor Dulquer Salmaan was asked if he would do a biopic on his father Mammootty, here's what he had to say|date=7 August 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180808212459/https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-karwaan-actor-dulquer-salmaan-was-asked-if-he-would-do-a-biopic-on-his-father-mammootty-here-s-what-he-had-to-say-2646859|archivedate=8 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, he starred in ''[[Oru Yamandan Premakadha]]'' a [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam]] [[Romantic comedy|romantic comedy film]] directed by B. C. Noufal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/oru-yamandan-premakatha-review-a-bland-treat-with-feel-good-factors/article26966756.ece|title='Oru Yamandan Premakatha' review: A bland treat with feel-good factors|last=Sudhish|first=Navamy|date=27 April 2019|work=The Hindu|access-date=29 August 2019|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190428083912/https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/oru-yamandan-premakatha-review-a-bland-treat-with-feel-good-factors/article26966756.ece|archive-date=28 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> After ''[[Karwaan]]'', Dulquer Salmaan's next Bollywood movie [[The Zoya Factor (film)|''The Zoya Factor'']] released on September 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/reel/937828/the-zoya-factor-movie-review-also-known-as-the-dulquer-salmaan-factor|title='The Zoya Factor' movie review: Dulquer Salmaan shines in romcom starring Sonam Kapoor|last=Ramnath|first=Nandini|date=20 September 2019|website=Scroll.in|language=en-US|url-status=live|access-date=30 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190929134659/https://scroll.in/reel/937828/the-zoya-factor-movie-review-also-known-as-the-dulquer-salmaan-factor|archive-date=29 September 2019}}</ref> [[Abhishek Sharma (director)|Abhishek Sharma]]'s film adaptation of [[Anuja Chauhan]]'s novel ''[[The Zoya Factor]]'' didn't do well at the box-office but Dulquer Salmaan's performance was appreciated.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/reel/937828/the-zoya-factor-movie-review-also-known-as-the-dulquer-salmaan-factor|title='The Zoya Factor' movie review: Dulquer Salmaan shines in romcom starring Sonam Kapoor|last=Ramnath|first=Nandini|website=Scroll.in|language=en-US|access-date=9 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191004100037/https://scroll.in/reel/937828/the-zoya-factor-movie-review-also-known-as-the-dulquer-salmaan-factor|archive-date=4 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/the-zoya-factor-movie-review-rating-6012252/lite/|title=The Zoya Factor review: Dulquer Salmaan hits it out of the park {{!}} Entertainment News, The Indian Express|website=indianexpress.com|access-date=9 October 2019|date=21 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190926115643/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/the-zoya-factor-movie-review-rating-6012252/lite/|archive-date=26 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]'' stated: \"From being playful to intense, Dulquer steals the show as he is absolutely brilliant in his portrayal\".<ref>{{Citation|title=The Zoya Factor Review {3.5/5}: Sonam Kapoor starrer is a fun, frothy film that pits superstitions vs strategy and self-belief vs luck|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/the-zoya-factor/movie-review/71209819.cms|access-date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nDulquer Salmaan's upcoming movies of 2019 are the Tamil films ''[[Vaan (film)|Vaan]] and'' ''[[Kannum Kannum Kollaiyadithaal]].''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/dulquer-begin-work-bollywood-film-zoya-factor-77248|title=Dulquer to begin work on Bollywood film 'The Zoya Factor'|date=1 March 2018|work=[[The News Minute]]|access-date=23 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180812181455/https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/dulquer-begin-work-bollywood-film-zoya-factor-77248|archive-date=12 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/kannum-kannum-kollaiyadithaal-trailer-out-dulquer-salmaan-take-us-for-a-crazy-ride-1574518-2019-07-28|title=Kannum Kannum Kollaiyadithaal trailer out: Dulquer Salmaan takes you on a crazy ride|newspaper=India Today|language=en|access-date=29 August 2019|agency=Ist|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806130245/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/kannum-kannum-kollaiyadithaal-trailer-out-dulquer-salmaan-take-us-for-a-crazy-ride-1574518-2019-07-28|archive-date=6 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/dulquer-begins-shooting-for-oru-yamandan-premakatha/articleshow/64880323.cms|title=Dulquer begins shooting for Oru Yamandan Prema Kadha|author=Anjana George|date=16 July 2018|work=The Times of India|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180821220855/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/dulquer-begins-shooting-for-oru-yamandan-premakatha/articleshow/64880323.cms|archivedate=21 August 2018}}</ref> \n\nSalmaan will make his debut as a producer with Shamzu Zayba's romantic-comedy ''[[Maniyarayile Ashokan]]'' which is produced through his production company Wayfarer Films.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2019/oct/05/dulquer-salmaans-production-titled-maniyarayile-ashokan-2043382.amp|title=Dulquer Salmaan's production titled 'Maniyarayile Ashokan' - The New Indian Express|website=www.newindianexpress.com|access-date=9 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006171624/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2019/oct/05/dulquer-salmaans-production-titled-maniyarayile-ashokan-2043382.amp|archive-date=6 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/dulquer-to-play-a-cameo-in-jacob-gregory-film/articleshow/71359021.cms|title=Dulquer to play a cameo in Jacob Gregory film - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=9 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191004012413/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/dulquer-to-play-a-cameo-in-jacob-gregory-film/articleshow/71359021.cms|archive-date=4 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He is slated to star in the upcoming crime-thriller ''[[Kurup (film)|Kurup]]'' in which he play the tituar role of [[Sukumara Kurup]], also marks his second production venture.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/malayalam/dulquer-salmaan-next-titled-kurup-5283098/|title=Dulquer Salmaan's next titled Kurup|work=Indian Express|date=30 July 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180731154401/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/malayalam/dulquer-salmaan-next-titled-kurup-5283098/|archivedate=31 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/dulquer-to-play-multiple-characters-in-ra-karthiks-tamil-travelogue/articleshow/59144460.cms|title=Dulquer to play multiple characters in Ra Karthik's Tamil travelogue|work=The Times of India|author=Deepa Soman|date=15 July 2017|access-date=23 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180224070805/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/dulquer-to-play-multiple-characters-in-ra-karthiks-tamil-travelogue/articleshow/59144460.cms|archive-date=24 February 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2017/nov/04/imman-and-dulquer-to-collaborate-1691499.html|title=Imman and Dulquer to collaborate|work=New Indian Express|date=4 November 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171106134305/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2017/nov/04/imman-and-dulquer-to-collaborate-1691499.html|archivedate=6 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/heres-update-dulquer-salmaans-next-tamil-project-after-ok-kanmani-710958|title=Here's an update on Dulquer Salmaan's next Tamil project after OK Kanmani|publisher=International Business Times|date=4 January 2017|author=Anu James|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122144416/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/heres-update-dulquer-salmaans-next-tamil-project-after-ok-kanmani-710958|archivedate=22 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Dulquer Salmaan Collaborates with Joy Mathew for a Political Thriller |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/dulquer-salmaan-collaborates-with-joy-mathew-for-a-political-thriller-2333611.html |accessdate=5 October 2019 |work=News18 |date=4 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191005134030/https://www.news18.com/news/movies/dulquer-salmaan-collaborates-with-joy-mathew-for-a-political-thriller-2333611.html |archive-date=5 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> His next project as a producer and actor is an untitled film dubbed the \"Production No 3\" where he will co-star alongside [[Suresh Gopi]], [[Shobana]] and [[Kalyani Priyadarshan]].<ref name=\"Production3\" />\n\n==Personal life and off-screen work==\nOn 22 December 2011, he married [[architect]] Amal Sufiya in an [[arranged marriage]]. Amal comes from a [[North Indian]] [[Islam in India|Muslim]] family settled in [[Chennai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Mollywood-celebss-honeymoon-diaries/articleshow/11488151.cms|title=Mollywood celebs's honeymoon diaries|work=The Times of India|author=Shiba Kurian|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030193848/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Mollywood-celebss-honeymoon-diaries/articleshow/11488151.cms|archivedate=30 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/mammoottys-son-gets-married/20111223.htm|title=Mammootty's son gets married|publisher=Rediff|date=23 December 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304125605/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/mammoottys-son-gets-married/20111223.htm|archivedate=4 March 2016}}</ref> The couple has a daughter born in May 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/malayalam/dulquer-salmaan-and-wife-sadiqah-blessed-with-baby-girl-mammootty-becomes-grandfather-4642243/ |title=Dulquer Salmaan and wife sadiqah blessed with baby girl, Mammootty becomes grandfather|work=Indian Express |accessdate=5 May 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170506100725/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/malayalam/dulquer-salmaan-and-wife-amal-blessed-with-baby-girl-mammootty-becomes-grandfather-4642243/ |archivedate= 6 May 2017 |df= |date=5 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe has also been involved in several social service activities. He has acted in a short film as part of the Kerala motor vehicle department's safe riding campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/dulquer-salmaan-star-kerala-motor-vehicles-departments-short-film-produced-by-maruti-suzuki-651085|title=Dulquer Salmaan to star in Kerala motor vehicles department's short film produced by Maruti Suzuki|author=Anu James|date=19 October 2015|publisher=International Business Times|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160211071246/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/dulquer-salmaan-star-kerala-motor-vehicles-departments-short-film-produced-by-maruti-suzuki-651085|archivedate=11 February 2016}}</ref> He donated 150 items, including clothing, shoes, books, school supplies and crockery items, as a part of the Chennai Gives initiative.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/Dulquer-donates-150-items-to-Chennai-Gives-initiative/articleshow/48836282.cms|title=Dulquer donates 150 items to Chennai Gives initiative|author=Asha Prakash|date=5 September 2015|work=The Times of India|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160730051213/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/Dulquer-donates-150-items-to-Chennai-Gives-initiative/articleshow/48836282.cms|archivedate=30 July 2016|url-status=dead|df=}}</ref> In addition, he is the owner of a web portal for trading cars and a dental business chain in Chennai.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/did-you-know-/Dulquer-Salmaan-ran-a-web-portal-for-car-trading/articleshow/47814873.cms|title=Dulquer Salmaan ran a web portal for car trading|date=25 June 2015|work=The Times of India|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150629141622/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/did-you-know-/Dulquer-Salmaan-ran-a-web-portal-for-car-trading/articleshow/47814873.cms|archivedate=29 June 2015}}</ref> He also is the director of the [[Bangalore]]-based Motherhood Hospital.<ref name=\"DoB\" />\n\n==In the media==\nSalmaan was ranked 4th by [[GQ]] in their listing of the 50 most influential young Indians of 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gqindia.com/galleries/50-most-influential-young-indians-performers|title=50 Most Influential Young Indians: Performers|last=|first=|date=|website=GQ India|language=en-IN|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/dulquer-salmaan-among-the-50-most-influential-young-indians.html|title=Proud moment: Dulquer Salmaan among the 50 most influential young Indians|last=|first=|date=|website=OnManorama|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724164114/https://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/dulquer-salmaan-among-the-50-most-influential-young-indians.html|archive-date=24 July 2019|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.mathrubhumi.com/movies-music/movie-news/great-news-dulquer-among-most-influential-young-indians-english-news-1.1177402|title=Great news: Dulquer among Most Influential Young Indians|last=|first=|date=|website=Mathrubhumi|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191012071317/https://english.mathrubhumi.com/movies-music/movie-news/great-news-dulquer-among-most-influential-young-indians-english-news-1.1177402|archive-date=12 October 2019|access-date=12 October 2019}}</ref> He was also featured by [[GQ]] in their listing of the Best Dressed Men India 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.in/fashion/content/dulquer-salmaan-interview-growing-up-a-star-kid-mam